[[[description]]]
This opcode node type (see the [`znode_op`](https://phpinternals.net/docs/znode_op) type) is used for simple variables in PHP code. For example, the variable `$a` is considered to be a simple variable, however the variable `$obj->a` is not (it is instead an [`IS_VAR`](https://phpinternals.net/docs/is_var) type). It was introduced in PHP 5.1 under the Compiled Variables optimisation.

